      padding: 1.5rem;
      background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
      border: 1px solid #1e293b;
      border-radius: 8px;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: #64748b;
      text-align: center;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .verdict-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
      .verdict-result { grid-column: span 1; flex-direction: column; text-align: center; }
      .study-title { font-size: 2rem; }
      .data-table-wrapper { overflow-x: auto; }
      .sensitivity-matrix { font-size: 0.8rem; }
      .sensitivity-matrix th, .sensitivity-matrix td { padding: 0.5rem 0.25rem; }
    }
  </style>

  <main class="container">
    <header class="study-header">
      <div class="study-meta">Compiled by Gemini 3.1</div>
      <h1 class="study-title">AbbVie Inc. (ABBV)</h1>
      <div class="study-subtitle">Intrinsic Value Estimate & DCF Analysis</div>
    </header>

    <div class="verdict-card">
      <div class="verdict-grid">
        <div class="verdict-item">
          <div class="verdict-label">Current Price</div>
          <div class="verdict-value">{formatCurrency(currentPrice)}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="verdict-item">
          <div class="verdict-label">Intrinsic Value</div>
          <div class="verdict-value" style="color: #4a8fe7;">{formatCurrency(intrinsicValuePerShare)}</div>
        </div>
        <div class="verdict-item">
          <div class="verdict-label">Margin of Safety</div>
          <div class="verdict-value">{marginOfSafety > 0 ? '+' : ''}{marginOfSafety.toFixed(2)}%</div>
        </div>
        <div class="verdict-result" style={`background: ${verdictBg}; color: ${verdictColor}; border: 1px solid ${verdictColor}40;`}>
          <span>Verdict: {verdictText}</span>
          <span class="premium-discount">
            ({Math.abs(marginOfSafety).toFixed(1)}% {isUndervalued ? 'Discount to Fair Value' : 'Premium to Fair Value'})
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Valuation Methodology</h2>
      <p>
        This valuation employs a two-stage Discounted Cash Flow (DCF) model to estimate the intrinsic value of AbbVie Inc. (ABBV). The model projects free cash flows (FCF) for a 5-year explicit forecast period, followed by a terminal value calculation representing the firm's perpetual growth thereafter.
      </p>
      <p>
        By discounting these future cash flows back to the present using an appropriate Weighted Average Cost of Capital (WACC), adjusting for net debt, and dividing by shares outstanding, we arrive at an estimated fair value per share. The goal is to determine whether the market is currently undervaluing or overvaluing the core cash-generating capability of the underlying business.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Core Assumptions</h2>
      <div class="assumptions-grid">
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <h4>WACC / Discount Rate <span class="assumption-val">{formatPercent(wacc)}</span></h4>
          <p>An 8.2% discount rate was selected. This reflects the inherent binary risks in the pharmaceutical sector (clinical trials, patent cliffs), balanced by AbbVie's massive scale, robust dividend yield acting as a pricing floor, and its successful navigation of the Humira Loss of Exclusivity (LoE) thus far.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <h4>FCF Growth (Y1-5) <span class="assumption-val">{formatPercent(fcfGrowthRate)}</span></h4>
          <p>A conservative 3.5% annualized growth rate is applied. While Humira revenues are declining, Skyrizi and Rinvoq are exhibiting exceptional growth trajectories, effectively bridging the revenue gap. The pipeline in neuroscience and aesthetics supports low-to-mid single-digit FCF expansion.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="assumption-card">
          <h4>Terminal Growth Rate <span class="assumption-val">{formatPercent(terminalGrowthRate)}</span></h4>
          <p>A 2.0% terminal growth rate assumes that into perpetuity, AbbVie will grow roughly in line with long-term macroeconomic inflation and GDP targets. For a mature, mega-cap pharmaceutical company, assuming higher perpetual growth is historically overly aggressive.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Cash Flow Projections (5-Year)</h2>
      <div class="data-table-wrapper">
        <table>
          <thead>
            <tr>
              <th>Period</th>
              <th>Projected FCF</th>
              <th>Discount Factor</th>
              <th>Present Value (PV)</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td>Base Year (Current)</td>
              <td>{formatBillions(freeCashFlow)}</td>
              <td>1.000</td>
              <td>{formatBillions(freeCashFlow)}</td>
            </tr>
            {projectedFCF.map((fcf, index) => {
              const year = index + 1;
              const discountFactor = 1 / Math.pow(1 + wacc, year);
              const pv = presentValueOfFCF[index];
              return (
                <tr>
                  <td>Year {year}</td>
                  <td>{formatBillions(fcf)}</td>
                  <td>{discountFactor.toFixed(3)}</td>
                  <td>{formatBillions(pv)}</td>
                </tr>
              );
            })}
            <tr class="total-row">
              <td>Sum of 5-Year PV</td>
              <td></td>
              <td></td>
              <td>{formatBillions(cumulativePV)}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Intrinsic Value Calculation</h2>
      <div class="data-table-wrapper" style="padding: 1.5rem;">
        <div class="calc-step">
          <span class="calc-label">Cumulative PV of 5-Year FCF</span>
          <span class="calc-value">{formatBillions(cumulativePV)}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step">
          <span class="calc-label">Year 5 FCF</span>
          <span class="calc-value">{formatBillions(year5FCF)}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step">
          <span class="calc-label">Terminal Value <em>(perpetuity growth method)</em></span>
          <span class="calc-value">{formatBillions(terminalValue)}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step">
          <span class="calc-label">Present Value of Terminal Value</span>
          <span class="calc-value">{formatBillions(pvOfTerminalValue)}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step" style="border-top: 2px solid #1e293b; padding-top: 1.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
          <span class="calc-label" style="color: #c8d0de; font-weight: 600;">Enterprise Value (EV)</span>
          <span class="calc-value" style="color: #4a8fe7; font-weight: 700;">{formatBillions(enterpriseValue)}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step">
          <span class="calc-label">Plus: Cash & Equivalents</span>
          <span class="calc-value">{formatBillions(cashAndEquivalents)}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step">
          <span class="calc-label">Less: Total Debt</span>
          <span class="calc-value" style="color: #ef4444;">- {formatBillions(totalDebt)}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step" style="border-top: 2px solid #1e293b; padding-top: 1.5rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
          <span class="calc-label" style="color: #c8d0de; font-weight: 600;">Total Equity Value</span>
          <span class="calc-value" style="color: #4a8fe7; font-weight: 700;">{formatBillions(equityValue)}</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step">
          <span class="calc-label">Shares Outstanding</span>
          <span class="calc-value">{(sharesOutstanding / 1000000000).toFixed(3)}B</span>
        </div>
        <div class="calc-step">
          <span class="calc-label">Implied Value Per Share</span>
          <span class="calc-value">{formatCurrency(intrinsicValuePerShare)}</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Sensitivity Analysis</h2>
      <p>Intrinsic value is highly sensitive to changes in the discount rate and terminal growth assumptions. The matrix below demonstrates how the fair value per share shifts under different scenarios.</p>

      <div style="overflow-x: auto;">
        <table class="sensitivity-matrix">
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td class="matrix-corner">Discount Rate ↓<br>Term. Growth →</td>
              {growthRates.map(g => (
                <td class="matrix-header-row">{formatPercent(g)}</td>
              ))}
            </tr>
            {discountRates.map(d => (
              <tr>
                <td class="matrix-header-col">{formatPercent(d)}</td>
                {growthRates.map(g => {
                  const val = calculateSensitivityPrice(d, g);
                  const isBaseCase = d === wacc && g === terminalGrowthRate;
                  const colorClass = val > currentPrice ? 'color: #22c55e;' : 'color: #ef4444;';
                  return (
                    <td class={`matrix-cell ${isBaseCase ? 'matrix-highlight' : ''}`} style={colorClass}>
                      {formatCurrency(val)}
                    </td>
                  );
                })}
              </tr>
            ))}
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem; margin-top: 0.5rem;">
        <span style="color: #22c55e;">Green</span> indicates undervalued relative to current price ({formatCurrency(currentPrice)}). <span style="color: #ef4444;">Red</span> indicates overvalued. Highlighted cell is the base case.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Key Risks to Thesis</h2>
      <ul class="risks-list">
        <li><strong>Skyrizi/Rinvoq Disappointment:</strong> The current valuation relies heavily on these two drugs offsetting Humira losses. Any clinical setbacks or pricing pressures in the immunology space would severely impair cash flow projections.</li>
        <li><strong>Acquisition Integration Risk:</strong> AbbVie has grown aggressively through M&A (Allergan, Cerevel, ImmunoGen). Failure to realize pipeline potential from these expensive acquisitions could drag down ROIC and balloon the already significant debt load.</li>
        <li><strong>Regulatory Pricing Pressures:</strong> The US Inflation Reduction Act (IRA) allows Medicare to negotiate drug prices. As AbbVie's top drugs approach eligibility, unexpected pricing cuts could compress margins faster than modeled.</li>
        <li><strong>Interest Rate Environment:</strong> With over $67B in total debt, a higher-for-longer interest rate environment will increase debt servicing costs upon refinancing, directly reducing Free Cash Flow to equity holders.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <div class="faq-container">
        <div class="faq-card">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Why is the debt load so high?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">AbbVie's debt load is primarily a result of massive strategic acquisitions aimed at diversifying away from Humira, most notably the $63 billion acquisition of Allergan in 2020. While high, the company's strong free cash flow generation provides adequate coverage for debt servicing, though it does restrict aggressive share buybacks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-card">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Is the dividend safe given the valuation?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">Yes, currently. Even with Humira exclusivity expiring, AbbVie generates nearly $18B in FCF. The dividend payout ratio remains manageable, and management has consistently prioritized dividend growth as a core tenet of shareholder return.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-card">
          <h3 class="faq-question">Why use a 5-year model instead of 10 years?</h3>
          <p class="faq-answer">In the pharmaceutical industry, predicting pipeline successes and patent cliffs beyond 5-7 years introduces extreme error margins. A 5-year explicit forecast captures the immediate post-Humira transition phase, while the terminal value appropriately blends long-term pipeline optionality with generic erosion.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <div class="disclaimer">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> The discounted cash flow (DCF) model and intrinsic value estimate provided above were generated by an AI (Gemini 3.1) based on trailing financial data and specific assumptions. This is not financial advice, an investment recommendation, or an endorsement to buy or sell securities. Investing in individual stocks carries significant risk. Always conduct your own due diligence or consult a registered financial advisor before making investment decisions.
    </div>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
